{"word":"ἅλιος","slug":"ἅλιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἅλιος1</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἅλς</el>\n<p/><i>of the sea</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>marinus</el>, of sea-gods and nymphs, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἅλ. ψάμαθοι</el> the <i>sea</i> sand, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/> <hr/> <el><b>ἅλιος2</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἠλίθιος'><el>ἠλίθιος</el></a>\n<p/><i>fruitless, unprofitable, vain, idle</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>ἅλιον</el> as <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, in vain, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <a href='S:regular, regularly'>regul.</a> <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>ἁλίως</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}